Ekurhuleni Metro police acted on a tip-off on Thursday morning and seized narcotics worth an estimated R1 million. JOHANNESBURG - There’s been a bust at a drug laboratory in Brakpan. Ekurhuleni Metro police acted on a tip-off on Thursday morning and seized narcotics worth an estimated R1 million. One woman has been arrested in connection with the bust. The EMPD’s Wilfred Kgasago said: “A woman, who was with a three-year-old girl, was arrested. She claimed that the drugs belonged to her husband. We were unsuccessful in trying to get hold of the husband, and the woman will be charged with possession of illegal substances.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)